cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about monocular depth estimation using synthetic data and temporal constraints. The most relevant sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV) as the paper focuses on depth estimation from videos. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a domain adaptation approach to transfer knowledge from synthetic to real data. Additionally, the paper uses pose information to improve depth estimation, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with videos and optical flow.
